No. The underlying FILE data structure may contain a socket (or a file descriptor, or a buffer), but it is not itself a socket.

You can't pass a FILE * to a function that expects a socket (bind for example), and you can't pass a socket to a function that expects a FILE * (fclose for example). In the usual usage of the word polymorphism, you'd have to be able to pass a FILE anywhere you'd pass a socket or visa versa depending on which way you are claiming the inheritance runs.
